### password-setup.http
###
### Password Setup API scenarios
### Tests for password setup flow (request token, validate, complete)
###
### Usage: Use with IntelliJ HTTP Client or similar tools
### Requires: Variable `apiBaseUrl` defined in http-client.env.json
###
### Note: Password setup endpoints do NOT require authentication
###

### Test 1: Request password setup token
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/request
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "registrationNumber": "12345678"
}

### Expected: 200 OK with message "If your account is pending activation, you will receive an email with a new setup link."

###

### Test 2: Request password setup token with different registration number
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/request
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "jan.novak@example.com",
  "registrationNumber": "87654321"
}

###

### Test 3: Request password setup - missing registrationNumber
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/request
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - registrationNumber is required

###

### Test 4: Request password setup - missing email
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/request
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "registrationNumber": "12345678"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - email is required

###

### Test 5: Validate password setup token
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/validate?token=abc123def456
Accept: application/json

### Expected: 200 OK with valid (boolean) and expiresAt (datetime)

###

### Test 6: Validate password setup token (invalid token test)
GET {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/validate?token=invalid-token-123
Accept: application/json

### Expected: 200 OK with valid: false

###

### Test 7: Complete password setup
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "token": "abc123def456",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "passwordConfirmation": "SecurePass123!"
}

### Expected: 200 OK with success message and registrationNumber
### Note: Use a valid token obtained from the request endpoint

###

### Test 8: Complete password setup - passwords don't match
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "token": "abc123def456",
  "password": "Password1!",
  "passwordConfirmation": "Password2!"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - passwords don't match

###

### Test 9: Complete password setup - weak password
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "token": "abc123def456",
  "password": "weak",
  "passwordConfirmation": "weak"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - password doesn't meet requirements

###

### Test 10: Complete password setup - missing passwordConfirmation
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "token": "abc123def456",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - missing passwordConfirmation field

###

### Test 11: Complete password setup - missing token
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "password": "Password123!",
  "passwordConfirmation": "Password123!"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - token is required

###

### Test 12: Rate limiting test (should work on first try)
POST {{apiBaseUrl}}/auth/password-setup/request
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "ratelimit-test@example.com",
  "registrationNumber": "11111111"
}

### Expected: 200 OK on first request
### Note: Making more than 3 requests per hour for the same registration number will return 429

###
